Here's a complete example:

**XAML**
```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding SelectionChangedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:MyItem">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="*,Auto">
                    <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="16" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Status}"
                           TextColor="Gray" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <Label Text="No items found."
                   HorizontalOptions="Center" VerticalOptions="Center" />
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel** (using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm)
```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isRefreshing;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private MyItem? _selectedItem;

    public ObservableCollection<MyItem> Items { get; } = new();

    public ItemsViewModel(IApiService api, INavigationService nav)
    {
        _api = api;
        _nav = nav;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            Items.Clear();
            foreach (var item in data)
                Items.Add(item);
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // stops the spinner
        }
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task SelectionChangedAsync()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;

        await _nav.GoToAsync(nameof(DetailPage),
            new Dictionary<string, object> { ["Item"] = SelectedItem });

        SelectedItem = null; // deselect so the same row can be tapped again
    }
}
```

**Key bindings explained:**

| Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` ã `bool` | Two-way: MAUI sets `true` on pull; you set `false` when done |
| `Command` ã `RefreshCommand` | Fires your reload logic |
| `ItemsSource` ã `ObservableCollection` | Auto-updates UI on add/remove |
| `SelectionMode="Single"` | Only one item selectable at a time |
| `SelectedItem` ã `MyItem?` | Two-way: holds the tapped item |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | Fires on tap ã navigate, then null out `SelectedItem` |

**Two things people commonly miss:**
1. **Set `IsRefreshing = false`** in a `finally` block ã otherwise the spinner hangs on errors.
2. **Null out `SelectedItem`** after navigation ã otherwise tapping the same row a second time won't fire the command (the value hasn't "changed").
